nce Solutions provides property and casualty insurance products to small and mediumsized businesses. Their products are offered through select independent agents in the Northwest and Southwest regions of the United States.</p>\r\n',NULL,'Injury.jpg','Blank.gif',NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,'cis',11,'Equipment Breakdown ','equipment-breakdown-hallmark-financial-services','equipment-breakdown-hallmark-financial-services','Equipment Breakdown - Hallmark Financial Services','Equipment Breakdown - Hallmark Financial Services','Equipment Breakdown','Equipment Breakdown',1,0,1,1,1,'2016-12-12 06:17:44','2017-09-19 19:42:31','<p>From large manufacturing operations to small retail stores, no business can afford losses to their mechanical, electrical or pressure equipment. Although more common than a fire, these equipment failures are not covered by many standard businessowners and commercial property policies. Warranties and maintenance contracts may have gaps as well. Typically, they do not cover accidents to equipment caused by operator error, business interruption, extra expenses, or spoilage losses which can result from an equipment failure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Hallmark CIS includes Equipment Breakdown Coverage on BOP policies as well as most Monoline and Commercial Package at no additional charge.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Equipment breakdown coverage addresses these gaps.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment breakdown coverage responds to the cost to repair or replace mechanical, electrical or pressure systems equipment that suffers a breakdown.<br />\r\nIn addition, indirect losses arising from a covered equipment breakdown that result in additional losses; such as, business interruption, extra expense and<br />\r\nspoilage can be covered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipment breakdown coverage provides the financial protection your insured need to run their business and continue to meet customer demands without worry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Exposures Examples:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	